Executive Profile
Jonathon S. Jacobson  Co-Founder, Chief Executive Officer, Chief Investment Officer, and Managing Director, Highfields Capital Management, LPAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships55--
Background

		Mr. Jonathon S. Jacobson Co-Founded Highfields Capital Management, LP. in 1998 and serves as its Chief Executive Officer, Chief Investment Officer and Managing Director. Mr. Jacobson served as a Senior Equity Portfolio Manager of Harvard Management Co. for eight years where he managed $2.0 billion in U.S. and international equities. From 1987 to 1990, Mr. Jacobson served as a Vice President of Equity Arbitrage Group at Shearson Lehman Brothers in New York, where he managed ... a proprietary trading account focused on options-oriented arbitrage strategies. He serves as Manager of Clear Channel Capital I, LLC. He serves as a Director at iHeartCommunications, Inc. (formerly Clear Channel Communications). He has been a Director at CC Media Holdings, Inc. He has been Independent Director of iHeartMedia, Inc. since July 30, 2008. He serves as a Trustee of Gilman School. He serves on the Boards of birthright Israel and Facing History and Ourselves. Mr. Jacobson received an M.B.A. from Harvard Business School in 1987 and graduated Magna Cum Laude with a B.S. in Economics from The Wharton School, University of Pennsylvania in 1983.Read Full Background




