nerally results in fairly long holding periods for Highfields; Jonathon Jacobson has claimed that a holding period can be two to three years. Between September 2011 and September 2012 the same three stocks have held the top three slots in the fund’s 13F portfolio according to our database of filings, and two more of the most recent top six had Highfields report a position of at least $200 million a year earlier.  Show More                    Fund Profile  Filing Period:  2017-06-30 2017-03-31 2016-12-31 2016-09-30 2016-06-30 2016-03-31 2015-12-31 2015-09-30 2015-06-30 2015-03-31 2014-12-31 2014-09-30 2014-06-30 2014-03-31 2013-12-31 2013-09-30 2013-06-30 2013-03-31 2012-12-31 2012-09-30 2012-06-30 2012-03-31 2011-12-31 2011-09-30 2011-06-30 2011-03-31 2010-12-31          Fund Name: Highfields Capital Management   Manager Jonathon Jacobson   Portfolio Value $10,785,382,000   Change This QTR +0.89%                 Top Holdings  Login to See All Holdings | Sign up      Filing Period:  2017-06-30 2017-03-31 2016-12-31 2016-09-30 2016-06-30 2016-03-31 2015-12-31 2015-09-30 2015-06-30 2015-03-31 2014-12-31 2014-09-30 2014-06-30 2014-03-31 2013-12-31 2013-09-30 2013-06-30 2013-03-31 2012-12-31 2012-09-30 2012-06-30 2012-03-31 2011-12-31 2011-09-30 2011-06-30 2011-03-31 2010-12-31     Last updated on May 15, 2017, 8:20 pm based on SEC 13F filings Last update: May 15, 2017, 8:20 pm              No.  Security  Ticker  Shares  Value (x$1000)  Activity  % Port      1. Franklin Resources Inc BEN 22,131,576 $932,625 +3% 8.64%   2. Marriott International Inc MAR 8,657,795 $815,391 -21% 7.56%   3. American Tower Corp AMT 5,672,243 $689,404 +1% 6.39%   4. Teva Pharmaceutical Inds Ltd TEVA 17,718,350 $568,582 +6% 5.27%   5. Hilton Worldwide Holdings Inc. HLT 9,425,148 $550,994 -67% 5.1%        Login to See All Holdings | Sign up, It's FREE        Latest 13D & 13G Filings  Login to See All Filings | Sign up       Company Symbol Filed By Filing Date Filing    Silver Run Acquisition Cor